<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1304,1547]" box="[151,572,1304,1331]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1304,1331]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
39.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1304,1547]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1340,1367]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Distribution.</emphasis>
Thus far only recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[687,783,1341,1367]" name="Belgium" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Belgium</collectingCountry>
(Pollet unpublished data), and southern European 
<collectingCountry box="[1355,1433,1341,1367]" name="Russia" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Russia</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,250,1377,1403]" name="Portugal" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: five northernmost provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1304,1547]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1413,1439]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ecology.</emphasis>
This species displays the same ecological profile as the strongly related 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" box="[1144,1270,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Medetera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis box="[1144,1270,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">M. muralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the rest of Europe, the species is less common and mainly recorded from dry to humid woodlands and carrs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1304,1547]" box="[199,699,1484,1511]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1484,1511]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
8.0 (fairly rare). Very rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1304,1547]" box="[199,713,1520,1547]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1520,1547]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Activity period.</emphasis>
May–June, August, October.
</paragraph>
